{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}
{% import "partials/_demo.njk" as ui %}

{% block title %}Meter · Stisla{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <header>
    <h1>Meter</h1>
    <p class="lead">A bar that visualizes a value within a known range.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Example</h2>
    <p>Memory used out of total, fuel against tank capacity, score against a target. Pair the value text with a label and the meter reads at a glance. Meter is the scalar-measurement cousin of <a class="link" href="/progress">progress</a>. Use progress when work is in motion. Reach for meter when the value just sits at a level.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="meter w-100" role="meter" aria-label="Memory" aria-valuenow="14.2" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="16" aria-valuetext="14.2 GB of 16 GB used">
      <span class="meter__label">Memory</span>
      <span class="meter__value">14.2 GB of 16 GB</span>
      <div class="meter__track">
        <div class="meter__bar meter__bar--warning" style="width: 89%"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Basic</h2>
    <p>Wrap a <code>.meter__bar</code> inside a <code>.meter__track</code>, inside a <code>.meter</code> root. The root carries <code>role="meter"</code> and the <code>aria-valuenow</code> / <code>aria-valuemin</code> / <code>aria-valuemax</code> attributes. The inner bar paints the fill via inline <code>width</code>.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-column gap-4 w-100">
      <div class="meter" role="meter" aria-label="Zero" aria-valuenow="0" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100">
        <div class="meter__track">
          <div class="meter__bar" style="width: 0%"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="meter" role="meter" aria-label="Quarter" aria-valuenow="25" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100">
        <div class="meter__track">
          <div class="meter__bar" style="width: 25%"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="meter" role="meter" aria-label="Half" aria-valuenow="50" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100">
        <div class="meter__track">
          <div class="meter__bar" style="width: 50%"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="meter" role="meter" aria-label="Three quarters" aria-valuenow="75" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100">
        <div class="meter__track">
          <div class="meter__bar" style="width: 75%"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="meter" role="meter" aria-label="Full" aria-valuenow="100" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100">
        <div class="meter__track">
          <div class="meter__bar" style="width: 100%"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Intents</h2>
    <p>Recolor the fill with an intent modifier on <code>.meter__bar</code>. The track stays on the neutral tier so contrast holds in both themes. Flip the intent at thresholds for a quick visual gauge. Success below half. Warning past three-quarters. Danger past 90.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-column gap-4 w-100">
      <div class="meter" role="meter" aria-label="Primary" aria-valuenow="60" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100">
        <div class="meter__track">
          <div class="meter__bar meter__bar--primary" style="width: 60%"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="meter" role="meter" aria-label="Success" aria-valuenow="60" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100">
        <div class="meter__track">
          <div class="meter__bar meter__bar--success" style="width: 60%"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="meter" role="meter" aria-label="Warning" aria-valuenow="60" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100">
        <div class="meter__track">
          <div class="meter__bar meter__bar--warning" style="width: 60%"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="meter" role="meter" aria-label="Danger" aria-valuenow="60" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100">
        <div class="meter__track">
          <div class="meter__bar meter__bar--danger" style="width: 60%"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="meter" role="meter" aria-label="Info" aria-valuenow="60" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100">
        <div class="meter__track">
          <div class="meter__bar meter__bar--info" style="width: 60%"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Sizes</h2>
    <p>Three sizes cover the typical range. Default sits at a thin strip. <code>--sm</code> compresses to a hairline. <code>--lg</code> grows to a label-friendly height for hero metrics.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-column gap-4 w-100">
      <div class="meter meter--sm" role="meter" aria-label="Small" aria-valuenow="60" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100">
        <div class="meter__track">
          <div class="meter__bar" style="width: 60%"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="meter" role="meter" aria-label="Default" aria-valuenow="60" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100">
        <div class="meter__track">
          <div class="meter__bar" style="width: 60%"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="meter meter--lg" role="meter" aria-label="Large" aria-valuenow="60" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100">
        <div class="meter__track">
          <div class="meter__bar" style="width: 60%"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Stacked</h2>
    <p>Drop multiple <code>.meter__bar</code> children inside one <code>.meter__track</code> to break the value into segments. The track is a flex row, so adjacent bars sit next to each other separated by <code>--meter-segment-gap</code>. Widths must sum to no more than 100. Any remaining room exposes the track background as the unfilled portion.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="meter meter--lg w-100" role="meter" aria-label="Monthly budget" aria-valuenow="78" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100" aria-valuetext="$3,120 of $4,000 budget spent">
      <span class="meter__label">Monthly budget</span>
      <span class="meter__value">$3,120 of $4,000</span>
      <div class="meter__track">
        <div class="meter__bar meter__bar--primary" style="width: 32%"></div>
        <div class="meter__bar meter__bar--info" style="width: 24%"></div>
        <div class="meter__bar meter__bar--success" style="width: 12%"></div>
        <div class="meter__bar meter__bar--warning" style="width: 10%"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Legend</h2>
    <p>Pair a stacked meter with a <code>.meter__legend</code> row when each segment names a category. Each <code>.meter__legend-item</code> carries a dot that reuses <code>--meter-bar-bg</code>, so the intent modifier on the dot (or an inline override) colors the swatch and matches the bar above.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="meter meter--lg w-100" role="meter" aria-label="Macintosh HD" aria-valuenow="83" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100" aria-valuetext="203.95 GB of 245.11 GB used">
      <span class="meter__label">Macintosh HD</span>
      <span class="meter__value">203.95 GB of 245.11 GB used</span>
      <div class="meter__track">
        <div class="meter__bar meter__bar--danger" style="width: 2%"></div>
        <div class="meter__bar meter__bar--warning" style="width: 6%"></div>
        <div class="meter__bar" style="width: 7%; --meter-bar-bg: oklch(0.86 0.18 95);"></div>
        <div class="meter__bar" style="width: 60%; --meter-bar-bg: var(--st-surface-3);"></div>
        <div class="meter__bar" style="width: 8%; --meter-bar-bg: var(--st-muted-foreground);"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="meter__legend">
        <span class="meter__legend-item">
          <span class="meter__legend-dot meter__legend-dot--danger"></span>
          Trash
        </span>
        <span class="meter__legend-item">
          <span class="meter__legend-dot meter__legend-dot--warning"></span>
          Music Creation
        </span>
        <span class="meter__legend-item">
          <span class="meter__legend-dot" style="--meter-bar-bg: oklch(0.86 0.18 95);"></span>
          Documents
        </span>
        <span class="meter__legend-item">
          <span class="meter__legend-dot" style="--meter-bar-bg: var(--st-surface-3);"></span>
          Calculating&hellip;
        </span>
        <span class="meter__legend-item">
          <span class="meter__legend-dot" style="--meter-bar-bg: var(--st-muted-foreground);"></span>
          macOS
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Customization</h2>
    <p>Override the variables on <code>.meter</code> itself, on a parent scope, or on <code>:root</code>. The cascade scopes the change. Size modifiers <code>--sm</code> / <code>--lg</code> retune the track height in their own scope.</p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Variable</th>
          <th>Use</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--meter-height</code></td>
          <td>Track height (8 at default density; sm 4, lg 16)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--meter-radius</code></td>
          <td>Track corner radius (pill; opts out of <code>--st-radius</code>)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--meter-margin-bottom</code></td>
          <td>Trailing space below the component</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--meter-header-gap</code></td>
          <td>Space between the caption row and the track</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--meter-segment-gap</code></td>
          <td>Gap between adjacent bars in a stacked track</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--meter-bg</code></td>
          <td>Track background (unfilled portion)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--meter-bar-bg</code></td>
          <td>Bar fill (intent modifiers retune; also drives the legend dot)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--meter-label-font-size</code></td>
          <td>Caption font size (label and value)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--meter-label-font-weight</code></td>
          <td>Label weight (value stays at the inherited weight)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--meter-label-color</code></td>
          <td>Label text color</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--meter-value-color</code></td>
          <td>Value text color</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--meter-legend-row-gap</code></td>
          <td>Space between the track and the legend</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--meter-legend-item-gap</code></td>
          <td>Horizontal gap between legend items</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--meter-legend-dot-size</code></td>
          <td>Diameter of the legend swatch</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--meter-legend-font-size</code></td>
          <td>Legend text size</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--meter-legend-color</code></td>
          <td>Legend text color</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>Track opts out of <code>--st-radius</code>. Pill is semantic for a meter strip and matches the rest of the bar family (badge, progress, slider). Override <code>--meter-radius</code> per-component for a brutalist square track.</p>
  </section>
{% endblock %}
